>☧\u003C/g>\n    \u003Clb n=\"5\"/>\u003Cw>ἐτελεύτησεν\u003C/w>\n    \u003Clb n=\"6\"/>\u003Cw>τῇ\u003C/w> \u003Cw>πρὸ\u003C/w> \u003Cnum value=\"15\">ιε\u003C/num> \u003Cg ref=\"#dipunct\">:\u003C/g> \u003Cw>\u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>Κα\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>λανδῶν\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan>\u003C/w> \u003Cw>\u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>Μαρ\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>τίων\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan>\u003C/w>\n  \u003C/ab>\n\u003C/div>",{"n":94,"url":95,"height":96,"width":97,"desc":98,"surfaceType":99},[145,162],[131,141,146],[147,163],[175,176,4,19,24,28,177,178,179,180,178,181,182,118],"isic003281","epitaph for bassos","catina","catania","italy","sicily","museo civico di catania","ancient greek",{"title":184,"body":185,"divs":186,"images":207},"ISic003281. Epitaph for Bassos","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Ἐνθάδε κεῖτε \u003Cbr id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Βάσσος ἰατρός \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ἔζησεν ἔτη \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ν´ christogram \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>ἐτελεύτησεν \u003Cbr id=\"al6-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>τῇ πρὸ ιε´ : Κα(λανδῶν) Μαρ(τίων) \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΕΝΘΑΔΕΚΕΙΤΕ\u003Cbr id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΒΑΣΣΟΣΙΑΤΡΟΣ\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΕΖΗΣΕΝΕΤΗ\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>Νchristogram\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>ΕΤΕΛΕΥΤΗΣΕΝ\u003Cbr id=\"al6-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>ΤΗΠΡΟΙΕ:ΚΑΜΑΡ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003281_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic003281_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003281.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic003281-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photograph\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Here lies Bassos the doctor. He lived for 50 years, and died 15 days before the Kalends of March.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Qui giace Bassos il medico. Visse 50 anni e morì 15 giorni prima delle Calende di marzo.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The epitaph presents the traditional expression \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἐνθάδε κεῖται\u003C/span> (for the phonetic development of \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">κεῖται\u003C/span> into \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">κεῖτε\u003C/span> from the 3rd cent. AD, see in Catania IG 14.532 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001351\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001351\u003C/a>, Libertini (1930) 44 no.7 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001629\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001629\u003C/a>), followed by the name of the deceased, the age and the date of death (in this case expressed with the verb \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">τελευτάω\u003C/span> in the aorist form), which is frequent in Christian epitaphs. In this case, there is the mention (rare in Christian epitaphs) of the profession of the deceased, \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἰατρός\u003C/span>. For other Sicilian inscriptions mentioning doctors, see Rizzo, F. P. (1989), \"La menzione del lavoro nelle epigrafi della Sicilia antica: Per una storia della mentalità\", pp.62-64 and Manganaro, G. (1994), \"Iscrizioni, epigrafi ed epigrammi in Greco della Sicilia orientale di epoca romana\", in \"Mélanges de l’École Francaise de Rome: Antiquité\" 106(1), 79–118, at p.107.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli> 1920 p.432 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001282\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001282\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 171 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Orsi NSA 1918 63 no.7 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 140 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000394\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000394\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Rizzo 1989 64 no.25 \u003C/li>  \u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli>  \u003C/li>  \u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[187,190,193,196,198,201,204],{"id":188,"html":189},"editions","\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Ἐνθάδε κεῖτε \u003Cbr id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Βάσσος ἰατρός \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ἔζησεν ἔτη \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ν´ christogram \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>ἐτελεύτησεν \u003Cbr id=\"al6-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>τῇ πρὸ ιε´ : Κα(λανδῶν) Μαρ(τίων) \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΕΝΘΑΔΕΚΕΙΤΕ\u003Cbr id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΒΑΣΣΟΣΙΑΤΡΟΣ\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΕΖΗΣΕΝΕΤΗ\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>Νchristogram\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>ΕΤΕΛΕΥΤΗΣΕΝ\u003Cbr id=\"al6-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>ΤΗΠΡΟΙΕ:ΚΑΜΑΡ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":191,"html":192},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photograph\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":194,"html":195},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Here lies Bassos the doctor. He lived for 50 years, and died 15 days before the Kalends of March.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":194,"html":197},"\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Qui giace Bassos il m